==English==

===Pronunciation===
'''By*zan-tine'''
{{rfap}}
BA&Iuml;-zahn-tyn

===Etymology===
[[Byzantium|Byzant(ium)]]

===Noun===
'''Byzantine'''

# (''Archaic'') A native of [[Byzantium]] which was in the same place as is now [[Istanbul]]
# (''Historic'') What belongs to the civilization of the East-Roman empire, as it was established after 331 A.D. when the capital was moved to Constantinoupolis (now [[Istanbul]]) and up to 1453 when it was conquered by the Turks.

===Adjective===
'''Byzantine'''

# Complex or intricate
# (archaic) Of or pertaining to [[Byzantium]]

